<headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 06 at 5:12AM CDT  by NWS Tulsa</headline>
<description>...Strong thunderstorms will impact portions of southeastern Haskell,
Latimer, central Le Flore and east central Pittsburg Counties through
545 AM CDT...
At 512 AM CDT, Doppler radar indicated strong thunderstorms along a
line extending from 4 miles northeast of Mccurtain to 4 miles
southeast of Lequire to 3 miles west of Robbers Cave State Park.
Movement was southeast at 45 mph.
HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down small tree limbs and blow
around unsecured objects.
Locations in or near the path include...
Poteau...                         Wilburton...
Heavener...                       Talihina...
Wister...                         Howe...
Keota...                          Red Oak...
Mccurtain...                      Bokoshe...
Fanshawe...                       Kinta...
Talimena State Park...            Mc Curtain...
Lequire...                        Damon...
Bengal...                         Robbers Cave State Park...
Lake Wister State Park...         Heavener Runestone State Park...
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.00 IN
MAX WIND GUST...50 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
